SIMPLE: passivity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Passivity
<hw>Pas*siv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>passivit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Passiveness; --
opposed to <xex>activity</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The tendency of a body to
remain in a given state, either of motion or rest, till disturbed by
another body; inertia.</def> <rj><au>Cheyne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The quality or condition of any
substance which has no inclination to chemical activity;
inactivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pass-key</ent>⟦br⟧
